hare-button facebook\">\n            <span class=\"icon\">\n            </span>\n            <span class=\"action\">\n             share\n            </span>\n           </div>\n          </a>\n          <a class=\"button_google_plus\" data-full-url=\"http://allafrica.com/stories/201601040036.html\" data-height=\"600\" data-width=\"600\">\n           <div class=\"share-button google_plus\">\n            <span class=\"icon\">\n            </span>\n            <span class=\"action\">\n             Google+\n            </span>\n           </div>\n          </a>\n          <a class=\"button_comment\" href=\"#comments\">\n           <div class=\"share-button comment\">\n            <span class=\"icon\">\n            </span>\n            <span class=\"action\">\n             comment\n            </span>\n           </div>\n          </a>\n          <a class=\"a2a_button_email\">\n           <div class=\"share-button email\">\n            <span class=\"icon\">\n            </span>\n            <span class=\"action\">\n             email\n            </span>\n           </div>\n          </a>\n          <a class=\"a2a_dd\" href=\"//www.addtoany.com/share_save?linkurl=http%3A%2F%2Fallafrica.com%2Fstories%2F201601040036.html&amp;linkname=Bayelsa%20Election%20-%20Sylva%20Not%20Dickson%2C%20Attempted%20to%20Bribe%20Bayelsa%20REC%2C%20Group%20as%20Alleges\">\n           <div class=\"share-button more\">\n            <span class=\"icon\">\n            </span>\n            <span class=\"action\">\n             more\n            </span>\n           </div>\n          </a>\n         </div>\n         <div style=\"clear: both;\">\n         </div>\n         <script type=\"text/javascript\">\n          function my_addtoany_onready() {\na2a.init('page', {\ntarget: '.share-button.more',\nlinkname: \"Bayelsa Election - Sylva Not Dickson, Attempted to Bribe Bayelsa REC, Group as Alleges\",\nshow_title: 1,\nlinkurl: 'http://allafrica.com/stories/201601040036.html',\n});\na2a.getByClass(\"sharebar solid\",document)[0].style.display = 'block';\n}\n// Setup Lockerz Share \"onReady\" callback\nvar a2a_config = a2a_config || {};\na2a_config.tracking_callback = {\nready: my_addtoany_onready,\n};\na2a_config.onclick = true;\na2a_config.num_services = 8;\na2a_config.hide_embeds = 1;\na2a_config.orientation = 'up';\na2a_config.prioritize = [\"facebook\", \"twitter\", \"google_plus\", \"pinterest\", \"linkedin\", \"reddit\", \"digg\", \"delicious\", \"stumbleupon\"];\na2a_config.locale = \"en\";\n// Load Lockerz Share script asynchronously\n_ready.push(function($) {\nvar a = document.createElement('script');\na.type = 'text/javascript';\na.async = true;\na.src = '//static.addtoany.com/menu/page.js';\nvar s = document.getElementsByTagName('script')[0];\ns.parentNode.insertBefore(a, s);\n});\n         </script>\n        </div>\n        <!--/.sharebar.solid-->\n        <div class=\"useful-top\">\n         <div class=\"column useful\">\n          <div class=\"content\">\n          </div>\n          <!--/.content-->\n         </div>\n         <!--/.column.useful-->\n        </div>\n        <!--/.useful-top-->\n        <div class=\"content-container\">\n         <div class=\"story-body\">\n          <cite class=\"byline\">\n           By Blessing Obineche\n          </cite>\n          <p class=\"story-body-text\" data-para-word-count=\"67\">\n           The Bayelsa State Justice Forum, has taken a swipe at the All Progressives Congress (APC), over the claim, that the Governor of Bayelsa and candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), offered a bribe of two hundred million Naira, to the State's Resident Electoral Commissioner (REC), Mr. Baritor Kpagih to manipulate the outcome of the December 2015 governorship election in the State, in favor of the PDP.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"story-body-text\" data-para-word-count=\"39\">\n           The Forum through its Coordinator, Pastor Markson Konugha in a release sent to journalists in Yenegoa, described as false, spurious and baseless, the alarmist cry by the APC, accusing the REC and Governor Seriake Dickson, in the alleged scandal.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"story-body-text\" data-para-word-count=\"79\">\n           Reacting to the allegation, Pastor Konugha who laughed off the APC allegation being made through one of its front in INEC, Mr Francis Asmakia Tedobserved that while it was not necessary to join issues with the APC, a party which has already lost the governorship election in Bayelsa State, and is reputed to thrive on propaganda and blackmail, it was pertinent to set the records straight so that the unsuspecting public is not misled and misinformed by the APC.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"story-body-text\" data-para-word-count=\"48\">\n           The Group's Coordinator said the bribe story only exists in the imagination of its authors. He challenged the APC to present evidence of how the alleged sum of N200m was handed to the INEC's REC by Governor Seriake Dickson, through whom, and by what channel it was transmitted.\n          </p>\n          <div style=\"clear: both;\">\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"outer-ad-container responsive-aans-view-a-container\" id=\"responsive-aans-view-a-container\">\n           <!-- google ad container for 'AllAfrica_ResponsiveAansViewA'-->\n           <div class=\"ad-container google-ad google-responsive-ad responsive-ad responsive-aans-view-ad responsive-aans-view-a\">\n            <ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-2420009840005975\" data-ad-slot=\"3319981629\" style=\"display:block\">\n            </ins>\n            <script>\n             (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n            </script>\n           </div>\n           <!--/.ad-container.google-ad.google-responsive-ad.responsive-ad.responsive-aans-view-ad.responsive-aans-view-a-->\n          </div>\n          <!--/.outer-ad-container.responsive-aans-view-a-container-->\n          <div id=\"in-article-p-mid\">\n          </div>\n          <div id=\"aans-body-mid\">\n          </div>\n          <p class=\"story-body-text\" data-para-word-count=\"47\">\n           The group berated the APC for what he termed its provocative acts of mudslinging, in a desperate bid to manipulate the outcome of the rescheduled elections in the Southern Ijaw Local government area of the State, scheduled for January 9th, 2016, which it said, will not work.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"story-body-text\" data-para-word-count=\"71\">\n           The group also disclosed that it was aware that investigation is ongoing into the claim by Mr. Baritor Kpagih that some influential politicians attempted to bribe him before the December 2015 Governorship election, as information has it already, that the APC governorship candidate, Chief Timipre Sylva did actually approached the REC, through his wife with a cash sum of One million US Dollars which was out rightly rejected by Mrs. Kpaghi.\n          </p>\n          <p class=\"story-body-text\" data-para-word-count=\"42\">\n           The group however called on all Bayelsans and supporters of Governor Seriake Dickson to remain steadfast and continue to support the PDP administration in the state to deliver on its agenda of economic development, job and wealth creation, as well as industrialisation.\n          </p>\n          <div id=\"aans-body-end\">\n          </div>\n         </div>\n         <!--/.story-body-->\n        </div>\n        <!--./content-container-->\n        <div style=\"clear: both;\">\n        </div>\n        <div id=\"in-article-bottom\">\n        </div>\n        <div style=\"clear: both;\">\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"outer-ad-container responsive-aans-view-end-container\" id=\"responsive-aans-view-end-container\">\n         <!-- google ad container for 'AllAfrica_ResponsiveAansViewEnd'-->\n         <div class=\"ad-container google-ad google-responsive-ad responsive-ad responsive-aans-view-ad responsive-aans-vie